cs.NI, cs.CR, cs.SY, cs.DC, cs.DS

Reasoning: 
- cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) is the most likely category as the paper focuses on a testbed for vehicular networking.
- cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) is also likely as security is an important aspect of vehicular networking.
- cs.SY (Systems and Control) is relevant as the testbed allows for remote network control and distributed data collection.
- cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) is relevant as the testbed allows for cloud-based code deployment.
- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is less likely but still possible as the paper mentions distributed data collection and performance analyses.
